## When the error is "build returned None"

The geometry was constructed but the function forgot to `return obj`. Add the `return obj` at the bottom. Don't restructure the rest of the function.

## When the error is "wrong type" (returned non-MESH)

Probably `build_{{ lower_name }}()` returned a `bpy.types.Light`, `Empty`, or `Curve` instead of `Mesh`. Either:
- Convert: `bpy.ops.object.convert(target='MESH')` after construction
- Or rebuild via `bmesh` and create the object as `bpy.data.objects.new(name, bm_mesh)`

